Songs

Song 001 Amazing Grace
Amazing V-S! How I have found.
It wrecks a person's mind.
I once was found, but now am lost;
Could see, but now am blind.

V-S has taught my core to page,
And page my core it did.
How precious little I have done
Since I have I-P-Led.

Through many dangers, toils, and snares,
I have already come.
'tis HASP hath brought me safe thus far,
JES-2 will lead me home.

When I have run ten thousand jobs,
Each running as it should,
'till then I'll wait to praise V-S,
And say that it is good.

Song 002 The Battle Hymn of the Republic (No. 1)
Thine boss has seen the glory of the coming of the JES.
It is routing out the SYSPRINT where the datasets are stored.
It displays the lightning of his speedy R-J-E support.
HASP-5 is marching on!
chorus
Glory, Glory, HASPellujah,
Glory, Glory, HASP-'ill-do-ya,
Glory, Glory, HASPellujah,
HASP-5 is marching on!

A-A-A-Bend.....

Song 003 Auld Lang Syne (No. 1)
Should old Chuck Forney be forgot,
And HASP songs sung no more?
We'd shed a tear that times have changed,
And ask, what's now in store?

We'll hang our orange ties up now,
And padlock all our HASPs,
And bid our friends a fond adieu,
With one last hearty clasp.

We'll miss you Jim, and John, and Tod,
And Bob, and Bill, and Joe,
'cause stalwart workers like you all
Have made our project go.

We had our jokes on all you folks,
The one we did the best
Was when we said that HASP was dead;
We thought it was in JESt.

We gave you HASP-three-oh to try,
Complete with overlay,
But V-S had to come along,
and HASP had had its day.

When HASP commenced to be JES-2,
Some loyalists did stray.
They bid us all a fond adieu,
And went their merry way.

So JES-2 came and HASP went out;
It would never be the same.
JES-2-slash-HASP is really fast,
But what a cruddy name.

We're moving on to better things.
We know you'll not care much.
We'll always treasure all our friends.
We hope you'll keep in touch.

Song 004 Bicycle Built for Two (No. 1)
HASP team, HASP team, give us your answer true,
We're half-frantic at the lack of a shared HASP queue.
We might seem a bit myopic,
But ASP would be catastrophic.
It would be great, to communicate
With a HASP System built for two.

Users, users, what can we say to you?
We're just dying, to give you a little clue.
We might say it's under study,
but we'll level with you buddy.
We must concede, we've seen the need
for a virtual HASP for two.

Song 005 California, Here I Come (No. 1)
Real good throughput, here I come;
Not quite where I started from.
For HASP is, The Program
That makes it all go.
And O-S, When barefoot,
Does everything slow.

P-I-D, please don't be late;
That's cause I can hardly wait
To prove that HASP will be so great;
Real good throughput, here I come.

