Then one day about ten years later, a bold blue announcement proclaimed
that we'd soon be buying new systems
Three-Seventy was the new name.

It still had the same old instructions, and some new that we'd never seen.
And just to add to the confusion, the new reference card was not green.

Three-Seventy's Virtual Storage, runs with a DAT box you know.
The trouble is Virtual Storage, also uses a DASD that's slow.

V-S-2 is the new con-trol program.
