Song 109 Suicide Is Painless
Through early morning's fog I see
System dumps a-waiting me
It ABEND-ed at half past three
I'll fix it now with S-M-P.

But S-M-P ain't painless, it brings on many changes
It can be used with or with-out the "E".

I called up Level One to-day. to try to fix the o-ver-lay
They said that I would have to pray
That help would come a-nother way.

See, Level One ain't painless, they often appear brainless
They only queue you up to Level Two.

Level Two then rang my phone, but what they said caused me to moan
They left me standing there alone
"We cannot fix what we don't own".

Though Level Two ain't painless, it's sometimes even gainless
You can't re-port the problem on your own.

I did a search through INFO-SYS
Keyword searches - Oh what bliss
Fifty - fifty, hit or miss
Twelve thousand P-T-F's to list.

But INFO isn't painless
When it displays the changes
But sometimes it's the only friend you have.

In INFO-SYS I found a zap, I worried that it might be crap
I can't be sure that it will map
And Level Two won't take the rap.

But SUPERZAP ain't painless, the REPs are sometimes aimless
But you can't solve the problem without them.

The zap seemed to apply with ease,
but then the system tasks did freeze
It almost made the system wheeze
The cure was worse than the disease.

But code that's thus corrected
Can do the unexpected
Especially when run with zero keys.

I went back to the microfiche, instead of going to the beach
It took a second 'til I saw
A LOAD that should have been a STORE.

And I-B-M ain't painless, they never give you changes
Until they've got your system on the floor.

I-B-M, the moral here, which I hope I have made quite clear
This O-C-Only course you steer
Is not as good as may appear.

'Cause O-C-Only's painful
And I-B-M is blame-ful
If they with-hold the best kind of support.

