Song 126 The Sounds of Silence
Hello F-E my old friend., I have to talk to you again.
Because an ABEND soft-ly creeping, crashed the system while I was sleeping.
And the ABEND, that was hiding in my core.
For-ever more,
will be the cause of crashes.

Through endless dumps I looked alone, without an F.E. on the phone.
'Neath the halo of a tensor light, I looked at every single bit and byte.
'Til my brain was seared by the flash of an insight rare.
And then and there, I found the cause of crashes.

And in that spot of light I saw, ten thousand branches, maybe more.
Branches coded without any base, branches going into outer space.
Branches branching... where no code had ever been.
It was a sin,
this silly cause of crashes.

"Fools," said I, "You do not know,
Branches with no place to go,
Cannot make your super-visor run,
But can cut out all your weekend fun."
But my words-- like simple no-ops fell, down the well,
And echoed like the knell of crashes.

All Poughkeepsie bowed and prayed, to the systems they had made.
And the console scrolled up its warning, in the line that it was forming.
And the line said  "The code of the future is written in P-L-S,
Except for JES."
"About the source ... we're silent."

